code_changes.content:
{
  "buggy_files": [
    "drivers/ata/libata-core.c"
  ],
  "buggy_functions": [
    "ata_device_blacklist"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Samsung 860 EVO SSD is missing from the ata_device_blacklist in drivers/ata/libata-core.c. Similar Samsung SSDs (840 and 850) are already listed with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag to disable queued TRIM operations. The bug manifests as FPDMA QUEUED command timeouts during fstrim operations. The kernel attempts to use queued TRIM (ATA_CMD_FPDMA_SEND with DSM subcommand) on the Samsung 860 EVO, which causes 20-30 second lockups with 'SEND FPDMA QUEUED' timeout errors. The fix requires adding an entry for 'Samsung SSD 860*' to the ata_device_blacklist array (around line 4564) with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM and ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM flags. This will cause ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() at line 2218 to disable queued TRIM support for this device, forcing it to use the non-queued TRIM command (ATA_CMD_DSM) instead, which works correctly on this drive."
}

